Water Conservation Design Solutions

A design solution is a product or process that meets the needs of stakeholders. In our case, our design solution will promote water conservation.

1. Make a list of at least 5 water conservation design solutions that already exist in the text box below.

2. Now choose two or three of these ideas and build on them to make your own idea. Sketch your ideas in the sketch box below ("Design Solution Sketches"). You should only take one or two minutes to sketch each idea.

Look at the example sketch of rain barrels of different colors. This idea builds on the basic idea of rain barrels. Notice that the example explains the idea with a very simple sketch and a small amount of text that took about one minute to make.

3. Challenge yourself. Can you think of 5 design solution ideas, each building on an idea that already exists? Sketch your additional ideas in the same sketch box.

Today's Activity: Idea Generation

You just generated at least two ideas for a design solution. Great job! In today's lesson you will complete two different idea generation activities (called The 5 Minute Brainstorm and Collaborative Sketching). The goal of today's work is to think of design solution ideas and get these ideas on paper through sketching and typing. Do not worry about getting the perfect idea or drawing the perfect sketch. It is okay if you don't like all your ideas or if your work is messy. The goal of idea generation is to think of lots of ideas. Even engineering design professionals generate ideas they don't like or might not work during idea generation.
